</li></ul><h3>Rx4RDF
</h3><ul><li><a href="RxPath">RxPath</a>
</li><li><a href="RxSLT">RxSLT</a>
</li><li><a href="RxUpdate">RxUpdate</a>
</li><li><a href="RxML">RxML</a>
</li></ul><h3>Rhizome
</h3><ul><li><a href="Racoon">Racoon</a>
</li><li><a href="Rhizome">Rhizome</a>
</li><li><a href="RDFScribbler">RDFScribbler</a>
</li><li><a href="RhizML">RhizML</a>
</li></ul><p><a href="http://sf.net/projects/rx4rdf"><img src='http://sourceforge.net/sflogo.php?group_id=85676&amp;amp;type=1'/></a>
</p></td></tr><tr><td valign="bottom"><a href="http://rx4rdf.sf.net"><img width="100" style="padding: 0px" height="33" alt="Powered by Rhizome" src="rhizome.gif"></a></td></tr></table></td><td cellpadding="0" width="75%" padding="0" cellspacing="0" id="contentTableCell"><table width="100%" id="contentTable" height="100%"><tr><td valign="top" id="titlebar" height="1">index</td></tr><tr><td id="maincontent" valign="top"><p><a href="RxPathSpec">Rx4RDF</a> is a specification and reference implementation for querying, transforming and updating W3C's <a href="RDF">RDF</a> by specifying a deterministic mapping of the RDF model to the XML data model defined by <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xpath">XPath</a>. Rx4RDF shields developers from the complexity of RDF by enabling you to use familar XML technologies like XPath, XSLT and XUpdate. We call their RDF equivalents <a href="RxPath">RxPath</a>, <a href="RxSLT">RxSLT</a>, and <a href="RxUpdate">RxUpdate</a> respectively. 
</p><p>Building on top of Rx4RDF is an application stack that allows RDF to be used to rapidly build web applications:
</p><ul><li> <a href="Racoon">Racoon</a> is a simple application server that uses an RDF model for its data store, roughly analogous to RDF as <a href="http://cocoon.apache.org/">Apache Cocoon</a> is to XML. <a href="Racoon">Racoon</a> uses <a href="RxPath">RxPath</a> to translate arbitary requests to RDF resources, each of which can be associated with <a href="RxSLT">RxSLT</a> and <a href="RxUpdate">RxUpdate</a> stylesheets.
</li><li> <a href="Rhizome">Rhizome</a> is a general purpose content management and delivery system that runs on <a href="Racoon">Racoon</a>. It is dynamic and self-editable like a <a href="http://c2.com/cgi/wiki">Wiki</a> but uses <a href="RhizML">RhizML</a> and <a href="RxML">RxML</a> to enable structured content and editable metadata. This site is run on <a href="Rhizome">Rhizome</a>. <BR/><a href="RhizML">RhizML</a> is a <a href="http://c2.com/cgi/wiki">Wiki</a>-like text formatting language that lets you write arbitrary XML or HTML, enabling you to author XML documents with (nearly) the same ease as a Wiki entry. <BR/><a href="RxML">RxML</a> is an alternative XML serialization for RDF that is designed for easy authoring in <a href="RhizML">RhizML</a>, allowing novices to author and edit RDF metadata. 
</li><li> <a href="RDFScribbler">RDFScribbler</a> is another application built on <a href="Racoon">Racoon</a>. It is a simple web application that can display and edit any arbitrary RDF model using RxSLT and RxUpdate.
</li></ul><p>See also:
</p><p><a href="RDF">Why RDF?</a>
</p><p><a href="RhizomeStatus">Rhizome Vision</a>
</p><h2>Latest News
</h2><p>[29 February 2004]
</p><p>Version 0.2.0 of Rx4RDF and Rhizome released. <a href="RxPath">RxPath</a> has been completely reimplemented, much faster and robust. <a href="Racoon">Racoon</a> is also now much faster with the introduction of extensive caching. And, of course, several enhancements were made to <a href="Rhizome">Rhizome</a>. <a href="Download">Download</a> it or view the <a href="Rx4RDFChangelog">changelog</a>
</p><p>[15 December 2003]
</p><p>Version 0.1.3 of Rx4RDF released. Includes support for Python 2.3 and major
enhancements to <a href="Rhizome">Rhizome</a> -- including users, sessions, authentication and
authorization. <a href="Download">Download</a> it or view the <a href="http://sourceforge.net/project/shownotes.php?release_id=204244">changelog</a>.
</p><p>[18 October 2003]
</p><p>First public release of Rx4RDF. Get it <a href="Download">here</a>! </p></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" id="footer" colspan="2"></td></tr></table><!--(c) 2003-4 by Adam Souzis (asouzis@users.sourceforge.net) All rights reserved--></body></html>